title: Clinton server hack attempts came from China, Korea, Germany
text: Hillary Rodham Clinton's private email server, containing an electronic inventory of some 55,000 pages of emails from her stint as secretary of state, was repeatedly hit by attempted cyberattacks originating in China, South Korea and Germany in 2014, according to a congress ional document obtained by The Associated Press.
